---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Junho" description="Bio, contact, and resume highlights.">
	<div class="space-y-10">
		<header class="space-y-2">
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">About</h1>
			<p class="text-slate-600">A short introduction you can refine for recruiters.</p>
		</header>

		<section class="space-y-3" aria-labelledby="bio-heading">
			<h2 id="bio-heading" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Bio</h2>
			<p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				Replace this paragraph with your story: your focus area (e.g. computer science, HCI), what you're looking for
				next, and one or two concrete interests (systems, ML, product, design, etc.). Keep it tight—recruiters skim.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
			<h2 id="contact-heading" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Contact</h2>
			<p class="text-slate-600">
				Email{' '}
				<a
					href="mailto:junhohuh1234@gmail.com"
					class="font-medium text-teal-800 underline decoration-teal-800/25 underline-offset-2 hover:decoration-teal-800"
				>
					junhohuh1234@gmail.com
				</a>
				— also linked in the footer, along with GitHub and LinkedIn (update those URLs in <code
					class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm text-slate-800">Footer.astro</code
				>).
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3" aria-labelledby="resume-highlights-heading">
			<h2 id="resume-highlights-heading" class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Résumé highlights</h2>
			<p class="text-slate-600">
				Surface a few bullets recruiters should not miss; the full PDF lives at{' '}
				<a href="/resume.pdf" class="font-medium text-teal-800 hover:text-teal-900" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>resume (PDF)</a
				>.
			</p>
			<ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-600">
				<li>Education: school, degree, expected graduation.</li>
				<li>Experience or internship: role, team, impact in one line.</li>
				<li>Skills: languages, frameworks, tools you want to be known for.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>
